response.Q0: Generally, I would explore each of the initial 3 branches, and choose the most positive branch from there. Then I would click each of the two nodes that would branch out from there and follow the highest of the two paths, clicking each of the 3 final nodes. Then I would either choose the highest path, or if none off the paths were very satisfying I would move to the next best path so far.
response.Q1: Not significantly. In later rounds I found I tended to get options where none of the 3 final nodes were good options so I more often had to backtrack to the next best path.
response.Q2: I was happy that my initial strategy was reasonable so I didn't focus too much on trying to improve. I think I might have found it difficult to decide on the fly how to improve my strategy.
